author: National Geographic
description:
Born independent and adept predators of the ocean, great white sharks possess remarkable abilities. From their teeth-like scales to their deep blue eyes that roll back during an attack, here are five remarkable facts you should know about them.

Learn more about sharks in Jaws @ 50: The Definitive Inside Story, premiering tomorrow, July 10 at 9/8c. Stream on @disneyplus and @hulu.
title: How many Great White Shark facts do you know? 🦈🤔

author: National Geographic
description: Nat Geo photographer Jody MacDonald discusses the challenges faced when photographing the wild: "The wild never stays the same and that’s what makes it the ultimate creative fuel. Fast, slow, chaotic, still. It’s always shifting, always asking you to adapt. That unpredictability is what keeps me inspired as a photographer. Because when the wild is constantly changing, every moment becomes a chance to see differently."
title: Paid content for @toyotausa

author: National Geographic
description:
A 600-pound killer lurks, striking returning mother penguins with food for their chicks. Desperate to provide for her Rockaroni chicks, a Rockhopper penguin squares up against the Sea Lion, but will she emerge unscathed?
